  "title": "Microsoft Security Adoption Framework (SAF)",
  "contentHtml": "In this episode Michael and Mark talk with guest Mark Simos&nbsp;(<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://linkedin.com/in/marksimos'><i class=\"fa-brands fa-linkedin\"></i></a> <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://twitter.com/MarkSimos'><i class=\"fa-brands fa-x-twitter\"></i></a>)\n                  about new updates to the Microsoft Security Adpoption Framework\n\n                  <br>\n                  We also discuss Azure Security news about Secure Boot for Trusted Launch VMs, and the Microsoft HSM Toolkit.\n\n                  <br><br>\n\n                  <iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://player.rss.com/azsecpodcast/2975502?theme=light\" class=\"podcast-player\" title=\"The Azure Security Podcast\" frameborder=\"0\"><a href=\"https://rss.com/podcasts/azsecpodcast/2975502/\">MicrosoftSecurityAdoption</a></iframe>\n\n                  <h5>Links</h5>\n                  <ul>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://rss.com/podcasts/azsecpodcast/2975502/#transcript'>Transcript <i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i></a></li>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/topic/secure-boot-update-from-2011-to-2023-certificates-trusted-launch-vms-tvm-and-confidential-vms-cvm-845ec199-03fa-4629-bdc3-822ae0bbe6ca\">Secure Boot update from 2011 to 2023 certificates: Trusted Launch VMs (TVM) and Confidential VMs (CVM)</a></li>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://github.com/microsoft/AzureHSMEssentials\">HSM Scenario Builder</a></li>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/security/zero-trust/security-adoption-model\">Follow a security adoption model</a></li>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/security/zero-trust/microsoft-reference-architecture\">Review Microsoft Cybersecurity Reference Architectures (MCRAs)</a></li>\n                  </ul>"
